Bola Tinubu, presidential candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), on Monday, led the presidential campaign of the party to Gombe state. Pantami Stadium, the venue of the rally, hosted a large crowd of party supporters. Kashim Shettima, vice-presidential candidate of the party; Babagana Zulum, Borno governor; Inuwa Yahaya, Gombe governor; Abdullahi Adamu, national chairman of the APC, and Isa Pantami, minister of communication and digital economy, were in attendance at the rally. The APC entourage had earlier visited the palace of the Emir of Gombe, Abubakar Shehu Abubakar, for royal blessings. Here are pictures from the Gombe leg of the APC presidential campaign.             